<subSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" type="multiple">
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="147" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,862]" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
This species can be easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[788,933,296,322]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Cryptogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[788,933,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Cryptogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its elytral pattern and male genitalia. Elytra black, each with four yellowish brown spots arranged as in 
<figureCitation box="[989,1073,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
, penis guide on ventral view is relatively long and nearly triangular (
<figureCitation box="[571,655,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[623,655,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). The elytral pattern is unique and has not been observed in any other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[151,299,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aspidimerini">Aspidimerini</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[400,502,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.02" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="2.02">2.02 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[570,672,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="1.65">1.65 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[736,838,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="0.89">0.89 mm</quantity>
, HW: 
<quantity box="[909,1011,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="0.76">0.76 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.22, PL/PW: 0.39, EL/TW: 1.01.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
Body rounded, densely covered with white pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[859,945,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouth-parts yellow, clypeus light brown. Pronotum black except for a sub-triangular yellow spots at anterior corners (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1348,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Figs. 2b, c</figureCitation>
). Elytra black, each with four yellowish spots (
<figureCitation box="[588,666,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
a–c). Underside black except for abdomen and legs, partially yellow to dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
Head small, 0.6 times of pronotal width (HW/PW= 0.6) (
<figureCitation box="[851,930,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
a–c). Head with fine punctures, same size as eye facets, separated by 1.5–2.0 its diameters. Eyes densely faceted with small interfacetal hairs, interocular distance about 0.5 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[568,652,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
). Pronotum width 0.77 times of total width (PW/TW= 0.77), pronotal punctures fine, same as those on head, 1.0–2.0 diameters apart. Prosternal process distinct with two pairs of carinae. Elytral punctures coarser than on pronotum, separated by 1.5–2.5 its diameters. Abdominal postcoxal lines incomplete, extending to 4/7 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[638,722,835,862]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" startId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" targetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1789,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1789,1813]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Azad &amp; Wang" authorityName="Azad &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2020" box="[281,711,1790,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Cryptogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhalwalnensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,563,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis</emphasis>
Azad &amp; Wang
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[718,799,1790,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[718,799,1790,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1896,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1896,1922]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Penis slender, with apex curved outwardly. Penis capsule with inner arm well-developed, outer arm reduced. The length of tegminal strut nearly equal to the length of tegmen. Penis guide stout, in lateral view slightly curved inwardly, distinctly longer than parameres, in ventral view sharply narrowing to rounded apex forming cone shape (
<figureCitation box="[333,447,2004,2031]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,893,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-262@2.[151,1436,885,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cryptogonus bhalwalnensis Azad &amp; Wang sp. nov.: (a) habitus, dorsal; (b) habitus, frontal; (c) habitus, lateral; (d) abdomen (male); (e) penis, lateral; (f) apex of penis; (g) tegmen, inner; (h) paramere; (i) tegmen, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
Figs. 
<quantity box="[396,426,2004,2030]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
, i
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
